<statement>
<p>The measures of two angles of a triangle are <m>\displaystyle{79}^\circ</m> and <m>\displaystyle{43}^\circ</m>. Find the measure of the third angle.</p>
<p>  <m>\displaystyle\angle{C}=</m> <fillin characters="4" />°</p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>58</li></ul></p><table><tabular>  
  
    <row>
      <cell>
        <p>1.<em> Read</em> the problem. Draw the figure and label it with the given information.</p>
      </cell>
      <cell>
        <image width="33%"  pi:generated="problems/images/84e687113bcd9411edeaf4f3e13a909c.png" />
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        <p>2. <em>Identify</em> what we are looking for.</p>
      </cell>
      <cell>
        <p>the measure of the third angle in triangle</p>
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        <p>3. <em>Name</em> what we are looking for by choosing a variable to represent it.</p>
      </cell>
      <cell>
        <p><m>\displaystyle\angle{C}</m> =the measure of the third angle</p>
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        <p>4. <em>Translate </em></p>
        <p>Write the appropriate formula and substitute the given values.</p>
      </cell>
      <cell>
        <p> <m>\displaystyle\angle{A}+\angle{B}+\angle{C}={180}</m>°</p>
        <p> <m>\displaystyle{79}^\circ+{43}^\circ+\angle{C}={180}</m>°</p>
      </cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>
        <p>5. <em>Solve</em> the equation.</p>
      </cell>
      <cell>
        <p> <m>\displaystyle{122}^\circ+\angle{C}={180}^\circ</m> </p>
        <p> <m>\displaystyle\angle{C}={180}^\circ-{122}^\circ</m> </p>
        <p> <m>\displaystyle\angle{C}={58}^\circ</m> </p>
      </cell>
    </row>
  
</tabular></table>
</solution>
